            "command": "gh issue create --repo librefang/librefang \\\n  --title \"feat: MCP OAuth discovery and automatic authentication for Streamable HTTP\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\nMCP servers using Streamable HTTP transport (MCP 2025-03-26 spec) can require OAuth authentication. Currently, if a server returns 401, the connection simply fails. Users must manually obtain tokens and configure them via the `headers` field.\n\nThis feature request proposes **automatic OAuth discovery and authentication** for MCP Streamable HTTP connections, following the MCP spec's auth flow.\n\n## Motivation\n\nHosted MCP servers like [Notion's MCP](https://mcp.notion.com/mcp) require OAuth but handle the entire flow server-side — no client config needed. The rmcp SDK already parses 401 responses into structured `AuthRequired` errors with the `WWW-Authenticate` header. We should use this to drive automatic auth.\n\n## Proposed Behavior\n\n1. **Zero-config OAuth** — When connecting to an MCP server that returns 401 with OAuth metadata, automatically discover auth endpoints and run a PKCE flow\n2. **Config fallback** — For servers without `.well-known` discovery, allow optional `[mcp_servers.oauth]` config in `config.toml`\n3. **Token lifecycle** — Cache tokens in the encrypted vault, refresh on expiry, re-auth when needed\n4. **Non-blocking startup** — Daemon boots cleanly; servers needing auth enter \"pending_auth\" state\n5. **Dashboard integration** — Auth state badges in `#/mcp-servers` with inline authorize/revoke actions\n6. **Headless support** — Print auth URL to logs when no browser is available (Docker/remote)\n\n## Design\n\nA detailed design spec is available in the PR: [`docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-12-mcp-oauth-discovery-design.md`](https://github.com/neo-wanderer/librefang/blob/feat/mcp-oauth-discovery/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-12-mcp-oauth-discovery-design.md)\n\n### Key architectural decisions:\n- **Trait-based injection** (`McpOAuthProvider`) in `librefang-runtime` — no new inter-crate dependencies\n- **Three-tier metadata discovery**: `WWW-Authenticate` header → `.well-known/oauth-authorization-server` → `config.toml`\n- **rmcp `AuthRequired` error matching** — structured error handling, no string parsing\n- **New API endpoints**: `/api/mcp/{name}/auth/{start,status,callback,revoke}`\n\n## New Config Surface\n\n```toml\n# Zero-config (server supports discovery)\n[[mcp_servers]]\nname = \"notion\"\ntransport = { type = \"http\", url = \"https://mcp.notion.com/mcp\" }\n\n# Explicit config (no discovery support)\n[[mcp_servers]]\nname = \"custom-server\"\ntransport = { type = \"http\", url = \"https://my-server.com/mcp\" }\n\n[mcp_servers.oauth]\nauth_url = \"https://my-server.com/oauth/authorize\"\ntoken_url = \"https://my-server.com/oauth/token\"\nclient_id = \"my-client-id\"\nscopes = [\"read\", \"write\"]\n```\n\n## Related\n\n- MCP Spec: Streamable HTTP transport (2025-03-26)\n- rmcp SDK: `AuthRequiredError` type with `www_authenticate_header` field\n- Existing infrastructure: `librefang-extensions/src/oauth.rs` (PKCE), `vault.rs` (token storage)\nEOF\n)\"",
